headlines.description: — Paul George scored 12 of his 29 points in the third quarter and the Los Angeles Clippers ended a two-game skid with a 97-91 victory over the Dallas Mavericks on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: George, Jackson get Clippers past Mavs 97-91

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Detroit Pistons

headlines.description: — LeBron James was ejected for drawing blood from Isaiah Stewart's face, sending the superstar to the locker room early in the third quarter and leaving his teammates to pick up the slack.
headlines.shortLinkText: James ejected after bloodying Stewart, Lakers beat Pistons

video.headline: LeBron, Stewart ejected after LeBron swipes Stewart in the face

highlights.headline: LeBron, Stewart ejected after LeBron swipes Stewart in the face
highlights.description: After LeBron James elbows Isaiah Stewart in the face, both teams have to be separated multiple times. Upon review, James and Stewart are ejected.

events.name: New York Knicks at Chicago Bulls

headlines.description: — DeMar DeRozan scored 31 points, Zach LaVine added 21 and the Chicago Bulls rallied in the fourth quarter for a 109-103 victory over the New York Knicks on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: DeRozan, LaVine lead Bulls over Knicks, 109-103

headlines.description: — The Phoenix Suns rolled up 48 points in just the first quarter with a smorgasbord of 3-pointers, dunks and mid-range jumpers that buried the Denver Nuggets.
headlines.shortLinkText: Suns win 12th straight with ease, roll past Nuggets 126-97

events.name: Toronto Raptors at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Jordan Poole had his second straight 30-point performance with 33, Andrew Wiggins added 32 points and seven rebounds, and the Golden State Warriors beat the Toronto Raptors 119-104 on Sunday night with Stephen Curry's supporting cast taking pressure...
headlines.shortLinkText: Poole, Wiggins have 30-point outings, Warriors beat Raptors
